    "attributes": {
        "action": "Fund high-quality, non-partisan political and citizenship teaching resources",
        "additional_details": "This would help teachers feel more confident delivering these topics and ensure that lessons on democracy, government, citizens\u2019 rights and responsibilities, media literacy, and more, are taught to a high and impartial standard in all secondary schools across the UK. With the proposal to lower the voting age, and in an age of AI and algorithms, it is essential we make high-quality, non-biased political and citizenship education a right, not a lottery.",
        "background": "Youth Parliament UK urges the Government to invest in high-quality, non-partisan lesson resources that any teacher can use. It\u2019s vital students are taught the skills for informed and active participation in society, but too often teachers don\u2019t have the support, leaving students without consistency.",
